            "text": "Until recently , conventional culture techniques and immunofluorecence assays were considered the gold standard for the detection of respiratory viruses ,",
            "relation": "BACKGROUND"
        },
        {
            "id": 2,
            "parent": 1,
            "text": "even though results are mostly available too late",
            "relation": "COMPARISON"
        },
        {
            "id": 3,
            "parent": 2,
            "text": "or lacked specificity and sensitivity . <S>",
            "relation": "JOINT"
        },
        {
            "id": 4,
            "parent": 0,
            "text": "These methods are now widely replaced with appropriate DNA - and RNA - based amplification techniques , in particular real time PCR amplification , for the detection of an extended number of agents responsible for acute respiratory infections . <S>",
            "relation": "ROOT"
        },
        {
            "id": 5,
            "parent": 4,
            "text": "Real - time PCR offers rapid results , efficiencies in work flow and a reduced risk of false positive results",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 6,
            "parent": 5,
            "text": "due to contamination . <S>",
            "relation": "CAUSE-RESULT"
        },
        {
            "id": 7,
            "parent": 5,
            "text": "As a result , better patient management or reduction of unnecessary antibiotic administration will be possible",
            "relation": "CAUSE-RESULT"
        },
        {
            "id": 8,
            "parent": 7,
            "text": "leading to enhanced efficiencies in health care . <S>",
            "relation": "CAUSE-RESULT"
        },
        {
            "id": 9,
            "parent": 10,
            "text": "In applying molecular methods to diagnostic use ,",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 10,
            "parent": 4,
            "text": "the laboratory can optimise its diagnostic strategy",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 11,
            "parent": 10,
            "text": "by applying a combination of real - time amplification tests for respiratory viruses and the non - viral respiratory bacterial pathogens . <S>",
            "relation": "MANNER-MEANS"
        },
        {
            "id": 12,
            "parent": 10,
            "text": "However this must be done within a context of resource availability , technical expertise available and clinical utility . <S>",
            "relation": "COMPARISON"
        },
        {
            "id": 13,
            "parent": 4,
            "text": "It seems certain that molecular microbiology will continue to develop ,",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 14,
            "parent": 13,
            "text": "leading to further applications in diagnostic technology ,",
            "relation": "CAUSE-RESULT"
        },
        {
            "id": 15,
            "parent": 14,
            "text": "thereby improving our understanding of disease processes",
            "relation": "CAUSE-RESULT"
        },
        {
